@node "Install"
Please move the three Doors called

BGCHECK
EXAMINE
and
ARCCHECK (can be also renamed to FILECHECK)

into the BBS:SYSTEM/ directory

Now make sure that you check through all @{" SCRIPTS " link "SCRIPTS"} and change them if
necessary...
If you miss a script for a filetype then create it by yourself

*** Hint: If you had an older version of BelchCHECK then make sure that you
          check out @{" MOVE while upload " link "MOVE while upload"}

*** Important: All scripts must be placed in DOORS:BelchCHECK/SCRIPTS/
                                  
Now check through the @{" DOORS:BelchCHECK/CONFIG " link "CONFIG"} file
@endnode
@node "SCRIPTS"
*** Simple: SCRIPTS work like the s:startup-sequence

*** The Difference: You have so called VARIABLES which will be replaced
                    by BelchCHECK before it executes the scriptline

The following Variables will be replaced by the...

[-CONF-]     ...Conference Number
[-ELIF-]     ...Archive-/Filename ONLY but reverse
[-FILE-]     ...Archive-/Filename ONLY
[-HANDLE-]   ...Handle of the Uploader
[-LOCATION-] ...Location of the Uploader
[-NODE-]     ...Node Number
[-PATH-]     ...Archive-/Filename PLUS the path
[-PRE-]      ...@{" Prefix " link "Prefix"} of the Archive-/Filename
[-RANDOM-]   ...Randon generated number (Always 8 chars long)
[-SLOT-]     ...Slot Number of the Uploader
[-WORK-]     ...Work dir of the Current Node ("BBS:Node<x>/Work/")
                in this directory you can find the @{" FILE_ID.DIZ " link "MOVE while upload"}
[-X-]        ...Extension of the Archive-/Filename ONLY
[-XELIF-]    ...Archive-/Filename WITHOUT extension and reverse
[-XFILE-]    ...Archive-/Filename WITHOUT extension

The following Variables give only a SIGNAL to BelchCHECK for...

[-CLR-]      ...Clear Screen
[-DOOR-]     ...Execute a XIM Door ("[-DOOR-]s" would start the Status Door)
[-HIDE-]     ...Dont show the output of the following action

*** Important: The following VARIABLES are responsible for the
    Archive-/FileCheck

[-ERROR-]    ...that this line contains a possible Errormessage for the
                FileCheck routine
                You can enter upto *100* different lines with different
                Errormessages!

[-TEST-]     ...that the OUTPUT during the execution of this line must
                be compred with the Errormessages (FILECHECK!)

*** Hint: If you dont want to Check files then dont use the
          [-TEST-] and/or [-ERROR-] Variables
          And dont forget to take a look at the example Script files!

*** Hint: Of course all Variables and even the Errormessages are NOT case
          sensitive
@endnode
@node "CONFIG"
[-CLR-]     ...Clear Screen (Always_ON and not selectable as in the SCRIPT part)
[-CR-]      ...Put an empty line under the Descriptions (Requested by: Whiz!)
[-DIZ-]     ...Enter the full path to the File_ID door after this ("[-DIZ-]BBS:SYSTEM/EXAMINE1")
[-FREE_DL-] ...Mark files with this @{" Prefix " link "Prefix"} as a freedownload
               ("[-FREE_DL-]ATX" would mark a file with ATX as @{" Prefix " link "Prefix"} as a freedownload)
[-FREE_MSG-] ..Inform Users with a Message about freedownloads ON/OFF
               (";[-FREE_MSG-]" = OFF)

*** Comment: Caused by a technical problem of the Express it's STILL not
             possible to add a tagline under the Description...

[-MOVER-]   ...Background Mover ON/OFF (";[-MOVER-]" = OFF)
[-STRIP-]   ...Strip Corrupt Files to 0 Bytes ON/OFF (";[-STRIP-]" = OFF)
[-UPPER-]   ...Make FileNames Uppercase ON/OFF (";[-UPPER-]" = OFF)
[-BOSSNUKE-]   ...@{" BossNUKE " link "BiG BOSS"} FileLog Emulation ON/OFF (";[-BOSSNUKE-]" = OFF)
[-BYTEKILLER-] ...@{" ByteKiller " link "ByteAndi"} FileLog Emulation ON/OFF (";[-BYTEKILLER-]" = OFF)

*** Hint: If you use one of these nukers or both you can remove their original
          UdLog Door from the BBS:SYSTEM/ directory

[-BOBO-]       ...Forces BelchCHECK to use the Taglines config file from
                  @{" FileDescription " link "Bobo"} ("[-BOBO-]DOORS:FileDescription/FileDescription.Tagdata")
[-BYTEANDI-]   ...Forces BelchCHECK to use the Taglines config file from
                  @{" FileID " link "ByteAndi"} ("[-BYTEANDI-]DOORS:FileID/Sent.Dat")

*** Hint: Of course all Variables are NOT case sensitive
@endnode
@node "MOVE while upload"
Files will be only moved in the Background when AFTER executing the script
BelchCHECK can find the FILE_ID.DIZ file named as BBS:Node<x>/WORK/<Filename>
else the MOVER is automatically DISABLED and the file will be moved AFTER
the upload

So make sure that during executing the scipt the FILE_ID.DIZ file is
EXTRACTED, COPIED (...to BBS:Node<x>/WORK/) and RENAMED (...to <Filename>)

for LHA file is would work like this:
------------------ cut -----------------------
[-HIDE-]lha x [-PATH-] file_id.diz [-WORK-]
[-HIDE-]rename [-WORK-]file_id.diz [-WORK-][-FILE-]
------------------ cut -----------------------
@endnode
